Here's a response based on my own thought process. If I see an ad for a product or company I am unfamiliar with, I will not click it because I assume most of them are clickbait or something else more nefarious. However, if someone that I have connected with or have reason to trust describes a positive experience with a company or product, I am more likely to respond in a positive manner because some of the distrust has been eliminated. I kind of think it's why Amazon has such a hard time with fake reviews; people want to have reassurance that the product they are buying is working well for real people because otherwise it's just a waste of time and money and possibly worse. Knowing this, companies have worked to inflate their positive reviews, thus convincing people that it is ok to buy their product.
